trans-unit.source: Similar to fold, but returns a range containing the successive reduced values. The one-argument version cumulativeFold!(fun)(range) works similarly, but it returns the first element unchanged and uses it as seed for the next elements. This function is also known as partial_sum, accumulate, scan, Cumulative Sum.

trans-unit.source: Struct for creating worker-local storage. Worker-local storage is thread-local storage that exists only for worker threads in a given TaskPool plus a single thread outside the pool. It is allocated on the garbage collected heap in a way that avoids false sharing, and doesn't necessarily have global scope within any thread. It can be accessed from any worker thread in the TaskPool that created it, and one thread outside this TaskPool. trans-unit.source: Struct literals are syntactically like function calls. If a struct has a member function named opCall, then struct literals for that struct are not possible. trans-unit.source: System functions are not covariant with trusted or safe functions.
trans-unit.target: Las funciones del sistema no son covariantes con funciones confiables o seguras.

trans-unit.source: System functions are functions not marked with @safe or @trusted and are not nested inside @safe functions. System functions may be marked with the @system attribute. A function being system does not mean it actually is unsafe, it just means that the compiler is unable to verify that it cannot exhibit undefined behavior.
trans-unit.target: Las funciones del sistema son funciones que no están marcadas con @safe o @trusted y no están anidadas dentro de @safe funciones @safe . Las funciones del sistema pueden marcarse con el atributo @system . Una función de sistema no significa que en realidad no sea segura, solo significa que el compilador no puede verificar que no puede exhibir un comportamiento indefinido.

trans-unit.source: System specific code is handled by isolating the differences into separate modules. At compile time, the correct system specific module is imported.
trans-unit.target: El código específico del sistema se maneja aislando las diferencias en módulos separados.En el momento de la compilación,se importa el módulo específico del sistema correcto.
